</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legislation and Regulations</strong> - In the UK, the Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 mandate that employers ensure adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work. This includes provision for CPR training and equipment.




























